Implement every piece of work needed to make `13-file.loft` pass. This test exercises binary file I/O, file system operations, and several new language features around reading and writing files that do not yet exist anywhere in the codebase.

---

## What the test exercises

```
text_files()           — recursive directory listing (already works)
delete(path)           — delete a file; returns boolean       [MISSING]
exists(path)           — test whether a file exists           [MISSING]
move(from, to)         — rename / move a file                 [MISSING]
file("path")           — File handle constructor (already works via OpGetFile)
f#format = BigEndian   — set format                           [MISSING]
f += X as u8/u16       — binary append                        [MISSING]
f += "text"            — string data append                   [MISSING]
f#size                 — current file size                    [MISSING]
f#read(n) as T         — typed read; null on incomplete read  [MISSING]
f#read(n)              — bare text read up to n bytes         [MISSING]
f#index                — byte position of last read (both forms) [MISSING]
f#next                 — current read position                [MISSING]
f#next = pos           — seek to position                     [MISSING]
scope-close File       — OS file closed when var goes OOS     [MISSING]
```

